27304.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2ja4g","text":"Place a layer of dry ice in to box and add enough isopentane to make a slurry.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"arn6e","text":"Label embedding molds and add a small amount of CMC to each one (barely cover the bottom).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a5f5s","text":"Remove sample cup from ice and document on sample sheet the information on lid.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"htik","text":"Remove sample with forceps. Measure and document the length, width and height.  Document size and conditions (attachment)   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":122,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"3jhv4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"file","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"69DD511098E711E9AC243FD1B658C0A0","id":43724,"original_name":"Accession-Freezing Documentation.docx","placeholder":"/img/extensions/docx.png","source":"https://content.protocols.io/bkxve.docx"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fl8h5","text":"Place metal weigh boat on top of slurry and let cool.  Add tissue and cover box with lid.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3jov4","text":"Place embedding mold with CMC on top of the slurry.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"29v02","text":"Check the mold in the slurry to see if it is starting to freeze.  Add tissue when the CMC becomes only “tacky” on top.  Orient the tissue so that the side that is to be cut is face down.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"acbfc","text":"Slowly add more CMC on top of the tissue until it is covered.  Keep the lid closed over the slurry as much as possible.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"etcl1","text":"When completely frozen, wrap in foil and label sample number with sharpie.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"231eg","text":"Place all samples from one patient in a labeled box and place in the .","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":68,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"3cnrh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"A7A4CB40988811E9ABC96B49382B8BAC","id":"13787","label":"","protocol_name":"Freezing Fresh Tissue","step_guid":"555149A0985A11E995FBC7B29B8B149E","step_number":"12","temperature":"-80","unit":10}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"iecd","text":"Place disposable equipment in the Biohazard trash.  Wipe all forceps, rulers, bottles with appropriate cleansing wipes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"a5po3","text":"If fixing in formalin, prepare 1 large jar of 10% formalin.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2953e","text":"During step 4, carefully slice a small section of tissue (preferably having both cortex and medulla).  Do this in a way that you create two \"bookends.\"  The section for fixation should be no thicker than a nickel.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"ac8cs","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"2hir4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"C9506D80C9AC11E9AFE39FAD1D978862","height":285.3132075471701,"id":47079,"is_image":true,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/jpeg","original_name":"for freezing protocol.jpg","placeholder":"https://content.protocols.io/public/cac5dc7b8e855a6fc7a40981e89238df7c1037e3767a5311cd299b0874b5a9c5/bp9h6by6.jpg","source":"https://content.protocols.io/public/cac5dc7b8e855a6fc7a40981e89238df7c1037e3767a5311cd299b0874b5a9c5/bp9h6by6.jpg","width":208.0000000000002}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"a50cg","text":"Carefully place the piece of tissue into an embedding cassette. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cps98","text":"Tissue is then paraffin embedded by the pathology Core.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

27827.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"d4drk","text":"Mount sample onto the cryostat chuck using OCT in the desired orientation.  A flat surface can be shaved onto the mounting surface using a razor blade to ensure correct orientation and good adherence.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7upqt","text":"The angle of the stage should be adjusted to allow for a less acute passage of the tissue section over the blade as seen in the figure.  Acute angles cause the surrounding CMC to fragment and lose structural integrity.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"cia23","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"8trj3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"572ACD30D99811E9A04E8F776A62C1BF","height":248.4389534883722,"id":48166,"is_image":true,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/jpeg","original_name":"dave cryostat.jpg","placeholder":"","source":"https://content.protocols.io/public/cac5dc7b8e855a6fc7a40981e89238df7c1037e3767a5311cd299b0874b5a9c5/brbg6by6.jpg","width":406.00000000000006}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"796f3","text":"Trim CMC using larger section increments of 30-50 μm until the tissue becomes visible.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"17dr1","text":"Before procuring sections for imaging, the blade should be replaced as trimming can cause blade dulling.  This will diminish section quality.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dd66s","text":"Once the tissue is visible, excess CMC can be removed from around the sample using a precooled razor blade if necessary.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4ecrn","text":"Once a desired region for sectioning is reached, ensure the anti-roll bar is positioned appropriately.  It must not be too far towards the sample that it scrapes the tissue.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b786q","text":"Once the sectioning becomes reproducible and consistent, obtain the number of desired sections.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ft58a","text":"Manipulate each the section into position on a target surface (slide, ITO slide) using a fine tipped paint brush on the surrounding CMC material.  This prevents the contamination or disruption on the tissue.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ai6o1","text":"Once all sections are added to the slide, invert and gently press a Teflon coated slide onto the tissues to prevent wrinkles.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"2ec0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"5f1r3","text":"Flat sections thaw mount better than wrinkled sections, which thaw at different rates across the tissue.  This can cause tissues to stretch and fold, affecting the morphology and then resulting in artifacts in the imaging data.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cldf6","text":"Thaw mount the sections onto the target using heat from your gloved hand.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3hg1n","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"8banq","text":"Alternately, use a slide warmer at 20oC to expedite drying.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":37,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9u0g8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"134ta","text":"Once mounted, the section should be air dried immediately before returning the sample to the cryostat or vacuum desiccator.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dm0b4","text":"Add subsequent serial sections to the same slide until full for 3D imaging.  Take care to record any \"lost\" sections as they will affect subsequent data reconstruction.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7a0hc","text":"Carefully remove blade from container and wipe with ethanol and a lint free wipe.  Insert blade and lock into place.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

27835.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"cl958","text":"If sectioned tissue is frozen, return to room temperature (~20oC) within a vacuum desiccator (~30 min), otherwise proceed directly to step 2.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":62,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2k3p6","text":"Place microscope slide within adapter and insert into the Zeiss AxioScan Slide Scanner","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"91nr6","text":"Perform coarse focusing of the tissue using:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"b60t8","text":"DAPI filter set (ex. 335-383 nm; em. 420-470 nm, blue)  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"384mn","text":"Lamp power (~90%) and moderate exposure times (~150 ms)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"csk5f","text":"Perform fine focusing of the tissue using the following to build a focus map:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"1jo98","text":"DAPI (blue) ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"92u0n","text":"GFP (ex. 450-490 nm; em. 500-550, green)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"apsvj","text":"DsRed (ex. 538-562 nm; em. 570-640, red)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"27r0a","text":"Lamp power (~90%) and moderate exposure times (~150 ms)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7o1ef","text":"Define the imaging region that includes the tissue.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"87ppn","text":"Export autofluorescence image as an OME-TIF with the following options:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"1m0e4","text":"\"BigTIFF\"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"ecn98","text":"\"Use Tiles\"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"dlbdi","text":"\"Compress\"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"foh6j","text":"\"Convert to 8 Bit\"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"4m6nu","text":"Alternatively, other image file types, such as \"BigTIFF\" and \"pngs\" can also be useful, depending on the application.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

27877.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"54ls0","text":"Scann a 3200 dpi image of the matrix coated tissue section in the MTP slide adapter 2 with sufficient contrast to visualize the tissue boundaries.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"emfmi","text":"Choose a method that has \"height correct\" initiated upon sample docking. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"av4t3","text":"While the height correct profile is being generated, open FlexImaging and follow the prompts to designate sample file name, method, pitch, scanned image of the slide, etc.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7p7ic","text":"Once the height correct profile has been generated, train the target position with three teaching points following the instructions within FlexImaging.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cvpp8","text":"Draw a measurement region around the tissue for IMS analysis.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6c7vm","text":"Go to an area off of the tissue and ensure the focus of the laser is adequate for 10 μm spatial resolution imaging.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1l2o9","text":"Insert the slide adapter plate into the instrument airlock.  Then press \"load.\"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

27878.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"eg0qo","text":"Cut kidney in half along the longest plane and open like a book.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"4dvr2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"afckh","text":"Cut out a portion of the kidney (~80 x 60 x 4 mm) that is farthest away from the tumor location.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"49h3d","text":"Take a picture of the smaller piece of kidney in reference to its original location within the entire kidney if possible.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6cc0m","text":"Take only a picture of the smaller piece of kidney.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"96lk","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"3qrue","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9aej1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"CC8DDD00DBBA11E980459DBC171D14CC","height":249.44181818181818,"id":48322,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/jpeg","original_name":"Normal tissue-edit.jpg","placeholder":"","source":"https://content.protocols.io/public/cac5dc7b8e855a6fc7a40981e89238df7c1037e3767a5311cd299b0874b5a9c5/brgc6by6.jpg","width":329}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2go1j","text":"Cut the piece of kidney into ~4 smaller, rectangular pieces (~2 x 15 x 4 mm).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2cufl","text":"Image each of these smaller pieces in reference to their original position.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"84rg6","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"b49mb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"2F096EC0DBBD11E980459DBC171D14CC","height":262.0654545454545,"id":48323,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/jpeg","original_name":"Normal sectioned-edit.jpg","placeholder":"","source":"https://content.protocols.io/public/cac5dc7b8e855a6fc7a40981e89238df7c1037e3767a5311cd299b0874b5a9c5/brgd6by6.jpg","width":343.9999999999999}}}}

74843.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"flssd","text":"After the tissue has been imaged via MALDI IMS, the slide should be placed in a coplin jar or glass petri dish with a solution of room temperature 4% paraformaldehyde in PBS (*must be room temperature).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"r2cf","text":"Discard the PFA (the MALDI IMS matrix will come off the slide in this step).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a96ir","text":"Add fresh 4% PFA in PBS and shake for 5 more minutes (for a total of 10 minutes in PFA).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ofna","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cvt61","text":" Washing with PFA solution will fix and rehydrate the tissue as the matrix is removed. {"blocks":[{"key":"39i1t","text":"Add fresh PBS for 3 minutes on shaker.
